<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-116] AsyncProducer shutdown logic causes data loss</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-116</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The current shutdown logic of the AsyncProducer allows adding events to the queue, after adding the shutdown command to it. The ProducerSendThread drains all the data in the queue until it hits the shutdown command. Hence, all data added after the shutdown command is lost.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12519801">KAFKA-116</key>
            <summary>AsyncProducer shutdown logic causes data loss</summary>
